{"questionId":"9067452","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A molecule of citric acid, C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O<sub>7</sub>, is shown.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/ed4fd9807f2968831cf9c0c4b39bfc4c91f9569b.png\" width=\"215\" height=\"123\"></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The equation for the first dissociation of citric acid in water is</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O<sub>7</sub> (aq) + H<sub>2</sub>O (l) <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\rightleftharpoons \">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span> C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>7</sub>O<sub>7</sub><sup>−</sup> (aq) + H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup> (aq)</span></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The value of <em>K</em><sub>a</sub> at 298 K for the first dissociation is 5.01 × 10<sup>−4</sup>.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">State, giving a reason, the strength of citric acid.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">weak acid <em><strong>AND</strong> </em>partially dissociated<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>weak acid <em><strong>AND</strong> </em>equilibrium lies to left<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>weak acid <em><strong>AND</strong> K</em><sub>a</sub> &lt; 1 ✔</span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067452","referenceCode":"19N.2.hl.TZ0.4a(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The value of Ka at 298 K for the first dissociation is 5.01 × 10−4. State, giving a reason, the strength of citric acid.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 8: Acids and bases","8.4 Strong and weak acids and bases","Core","Topic 7: Equilibrium","7.1 Equilibrium","Core","Topic 7: Equilibrium","Core","Topic 8: Acids and bases"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}